title: User query: Plan description from client LLM
log: Create a Wayang plan that takes a text file containing organisation names, matches these names to the organisation table in the database, finds all departments belonging to those organisations, and counts how many “BS-opgave” tasks each operation center has. The plan must group results by operation_center and sort them in descending order. Output your result in a textfile.

operations.udf: (r: org.apache.wayang.basic.data.Record) => { val id = r.getField(0).asInstanceOf[Int]; val nm = r.getField(1).toString.toLowerCase.trim; (nm, id) }
(r: org.apache.wayang.basic.data.Record) => { val dep = r.getField(0).asInstanceOf[Int]; val org = r.getField(1).asInstanceOf[Int]; val oc = r.getField(2).toString; (org, (dep, oc)) }
(t: (Int, (Int, (Int, String)))) => { val dep = t._2._2._1; val oc = t._2._2._2; (dep, oc) }

log.thoughts: Read organisation names from a text file, match to organisation table, fetch departments for those orgs, join with BS-opgave tasks, aggregate totals by operation_center, sort descending via negated key, and write to a text file.

title: Class: PlanMapper Mapped plan finalized for execution

data.table: (SELECT organisation_id, name FROM organisation) as X

data.udf: (r: org.apache.wayang.basic.data.Record) => { val id = r.getField(0).asInstanceOf[Int]; val nm = r.getField(1).toString.toLowerCase.trim; (nm, id) }

data.table: (SELECT department_id, organisation_id, operation_center FROM department) as X

data.udf: (r: org.apache.wayang.basic.data.Record) => { val dep = r.getField(0).asInstanceOf[Int]; val org = r.getField(1).asInstanceOf[Int]; val oc = r.getField(2).toString; (org, (dep, oc)) }
(t: (Int, (Int, (Int, String)))) => { val dep = t._2._2._1; val oc = t._2._2._2; (dep, oc) }

data.table: (SELECT department_id, task_type, total FROM facttasks) as X
